The Kaya Forests will soon be destroyed if people are not barred from invading them, nominated Senator Emma Mbura has said.She joins an increasing number of people calling for the forests protection, citing their value as a tourist attraction and a way of preserving Mijikenda traditions. Respect for traditional values has diminished, Mbura told the Star on the phone yesterday.This comes a week after environmentalists, human rights organisations and elders in Kwale raised concerns about the destruction of the Kwale Baraza Park.The park is a tourist attraction. Kaya elders are pushing for its recognition as a heritage site under Unesco.Mbura said Jubilee will win over theMijikenda by preserving the forest. About 700,000 voters are from the Mijikenda community.